# ⚡ CivicPulse — Node.js / Express / MySQL Backend

Smart City Complaint Intelligence Platform REST API

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
civicpulse-backend/
├── server.js                   ← Entry point
├── package.json
├── .env.example                ← Copy to .env and configure
│
├── config/
│   ├── db.js                   ← MySQL connection pool
│   └── initDB.js               ← Schema creation + seed data
│
├── middleware/
│   ├── auth.js                 ← JWT authenticate + authorize()
│   ├── errorHandler.js         ← Global error handler + asyncHandler
│   └── upload.js               ← Multer image upload
│
├── controllers/
│   ├── authController.js       ← Register, Login, Profile
│   ├── complaintController.js  ← Full complaint CRUD + timeline
│   ├── analyticsController.js  ← Dashboard KPIs, heatmap, trends
│   └── miscControllers.js      ← Departments, Zones, Users,
│                                  Notifications, SLA Rules
│
├── routes/
│   ├── auth.js
│   ├── complaints.js
│   ├── analytics.js
│   ├── departments.js
│   ├── zones.js
│   ├── users.js
│   ├── notifications.js
│   └── sla.js
│
└── uploads/                    ← Auto-created on first upload
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### 2. Configure environment
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — set DB_PASSWORD, JWT_SECRET, etc.
```

### 3. Initialize the database
```bash
node config/initDB.js
```
This creates all tables and inserts seed data.

### 4. Start the server
```bash
npm run dev        # development (nodemon)
npm start          # production
```

